================================================================================
5. SELF-HOSTED EDITION SPECIFIC TERMS
================================================================================

(a) The Self-Hosted Edition is licensed by one-time payment for perpetual use,
    limited to the number of instances specified by the purchased tier.

(b) Updates and upgrades are included for the period specified at purchase
    (typically 6, 12, or 24 months). After expiration, Licensee may continue
    using the version installed but is not entitled to new releases.

(c) The Software contains a phone-home telemetry component that periodically
    contacts MAXIA Lab license servers to validate the License Key. This
    telemetry transmits only license metadata (key hash, version, instance ID)
    and does NOT transmit any user data, scan content, or PII.

(d) Disabling or blocking the phone-home component is a material breach of
    this Agreement and immediately terminates Licensee's rights.

(e) Source code is NOT provided with the standard Self-Hosted Edition. Partial
    source code access may be granted with the Enterprise Self-Hosted tier
    under a separate Source Code Addendum.

